==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Procephalic
<hw>Pro`ce*phal"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>pro-</ets> + <ets>cephalic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or forming, the front of the head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Procephalic lobe</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>that
part of the head of an invertebrate animal which is in front of the
mouth.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proception</ent>⟦br⟧
